stylometry: Our group project was finding the best way for Sally Beauty Supply to serve their customers the most efficient way and also best utilize their employees. The problem was that the customers were waiting in line too long when they had 2 seperate lines for the customers and we knew there was a better way to do it. So what we did was ran the waiting line models for both scenerios and compared the numbers to show the management that having only 1 line and having the next customer in line go to the next available register would be much faster. What we found was that using only 1 line decreased the average waiting time by almost 30%. What I learned from it was just how much more efficient it was to do this strategy in stores and that you always want your customer to be waiting less and shopping more so that they are happy because happy customers are paying customers.
